title: Launch Roundup – Northrop Grumman prepare the first Cygnus to fly on Falcon 9
summary: Recent challenges with weather concerns and the movement of key flights such as USSF-52 and Axiom-3 have impacted Falcon 9 launch dates, not least Starlink Group 7-11 which scrubbed three times and is now awaiting launch on Tuesday.

title: NG-20 Prepares to Fly to ISS From Florida
summary: Final preparations are underway for the launch of Northrop Grumman’s 20th commercial resupply mission to the International Space Station (NG-20), currently set to launch on January 29th 2024. This mission’s Cygnus spacecraft, named after astronaut Patricia “Patty” Hilliard Robertson, will be delivering food, supplies, equipment, and science experiments to the Space Station’s Expedition 70 astronauts 254 miles above the Earth’s surface.

title: Cygnus ready for first launch on Falcon 9
summary: A Cygnus cargo spacecraft is set to launch on a Falcon 9 rocket for the first time, a combination that required more changes to the rocket than to the spacecraft.
